Name: GDC Align
checklistText:
Note: 
    ATT SET SW should be in the GDC position when not undergoing this alignment
    Do NOT confuse ATT SET SW and CMC ATT SW. CMC ATT SW should be left in IMU unless an IMU failure occurs.

GDC ALIGNMENT TO IMU GIMBAL ANGLES
    IMU - on
        C&W Light ISS - Extinguished
        DSKY NO ATT - Extinguished
    SCS - operating
        P7 - BMAG PWR 1&2 (2) - on
        P2 - BMAG 1&2 Temp (2) - Extinguished
    Ordeal - Inertial
        P13 - FDAI 1&2 (2) - INRTL
    
    Damp vehicle rates

    Panel 1:
        ATT SET dials - set to angles on FDAI 1
            All written numbers on the FDAI are in the format (X)X0 deg. 

            V16 N20 E may be used to extract the correct IMU Angles in the format:
                R1: Roll 	(XXX.xx)
                R2: Pitch 	(XXX.xx)
                R3: Yaw 	(XXX.xx)

        FDAI Select - 1
        FDAI Source - ATT SET
        ATT SET - IMU
        ATT SET dials - null FDAI 1 err needles
            Align to current IMU Att, 5/1 FDAI Scale may be too accurate. Don't try to chase it with RCS.

        ATT SET - GDC
        GDC ALIGN PB - push untill needles nulled (aligned with indicated ATT)

        FDAI SEL - 1/2

Steps.Text: Set ATT SET dials to current ATT
Align Needles with current ATT on FDAI 1
